  "prompt": "What is the formula to calculate a synchronous speed of a motor?",
  "response": "The **synchronous speed** of an AC motor is the theoretical speed at which the motor's magnetic field rotates. It is determined by the frequency of the electrical supply and the number of poles in the motor.\n\n### **Formula:**\n\n\\[\nN_s = \\frac{120 \\times f}{P}\n\\]\n\n**Where:**\n- \\( N_s \\) = Synchronous speed (Revolutions per Minute, RPM)\n- \\( f \\) = Supply frequency (Hertz, Hz)\n- \\( P \\) = Number of poles\n\n### **Explanation:**\n\n- **Frequency (\\( f \\))**: This is the frequency of the electrical supply to the motor. In many countries, the standard frequencies are 50 Hz or 60 Hz.\n\n- **Number of Poles (\\( P \\))**: This refers to the number of magnetic poles in the motor. Motors can have different numbers of poles (e.g., 2, 4, 6, etc.), and the number of poles directly affects the synchronous speed.\n\n### **Example Calculation:**\n\nSuppose you have a motor with:\n- **Supply frequency (\\( f \\))** = 60 Hz\n- **Number of poles (\\( P \\))** = 4\n\nPlugging into the formula:\n\n\\[\nN_s = \\frac{120 \\times 60}{4} = \\frac{7200}{4} = 1800 \\text{ RPM}\n\\]\n\nSo, the synchronous speed of the motor is **1800 RPM**.\n\n### **Key Points:**\n- **Synchronous Speed** is ideal and assumes no slip. In practical induction motors, the actual speed is slightly less due to slip.\n- By increasing the number of poles, the synchronous speed decreases, and vice versa.\n- This formula is fundamental in designing and understanding the operation of AC motors, especially synchronous and induction motors.\n\n### **Additional Notes:**\n- For motors with **pole pairs**, the formula can also be expressed as:\n\n\\[\nN_s = \\frac{60 \\times f}{\\text{Pole Pairs}}\n\\]\n\nThis is essentially the same formula but considers pole pairs instead of total poles.\n\n**Remember:** Always ensure that the units are consistent when using this formula (frequency in Hz and poles as a whole number).\n\n**Reference:**\n- [Electric Motor Theory - Synchronous Speed](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Synchronous_motor#Synchronous_speed)\n\n**Summary:**\nThe synchronous speed (\\( N_s \\)) in RPM is calculated using the formula:\n\n\\[\nN_s = \\frac{120 \\times f}{P}\n\\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( f \\) = Supply frequency in Hz\n- \\( P \\) = Number of motor poles",
